y a different student every day over the PA system, then the school day starts and that's all there is to it. &#10;This 'is' Canada. Everyone of different heritage and religion makes up Canada however, we are 'all' Canadian &quot;FIRS.&quot; &#10;Canada is a nation worth saving as it is. It allows 'everyone' to retain their own religion and their own heritage while granting full citizenship. This is a great country that does this. This great country is Canada. &#10;Preserve your religion and your heritage while and be Canadian at the same time. Do this on your own time in your own space for the sake of conformity and keeping Canada a solid and sovereign nation, otherwise, we are going to be a nation of warring factions. &#10;Compromise for the sake of 'conformity' and keeping Canada a strong country &quot;is the order of the day,&quot; ... Let's get on with it. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1137" language="en" documentId="1383" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="williamrallis" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1383" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="20"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="21" end="145"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="146" end="409"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="410" end="527"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="528" end="746"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="747" end="1007"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="1008" end="1137"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>